House Resolution 806
By: Representative Jackson of the 128th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Morris Roberts; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, from an early age Morris Roberts has had tremendous musical talent and a
3 passion to share his talent with others; and
4 WHEREAS, throughout high school he participated in the Glee Club; was the marching
5 band's drum major and student director; played alto sax and was lead singer of the local
6 group, The Soul Sensations; and sang in the choir at Tennille Grove Baptist Church in
7 Tennille, Georgia; and
8 WHEREAS, when Morris served in the United State Marine Corps, in Okinawa, Japan, he
9 worked as a guest DJ at radio station KSBK, Naha, Japan, and he found a way to sing by
10 sitting in with various Japanese Bands; and
11 WHEREAS, singing is his passion; whether with the church choir, the bands of Okinawa,
12 local singing groups like Original Southern Travelers in New Jersey gospel group, open mike
13 nights, or talent shows, he would always find a place to sing; and
