14 WHEREAS, after his service, Morris started his own agency, MRPP Agency and booked
15 national acts around the country as well as opened the famed Peppermint Entertainment
16 Complex in Orange, New Jersey, and started a singing career of his own; and
17 WHEREAS, outside of music, Morris continues to uplift the community of Tennille by
18 assisting in political campaigns, education and alumni affairs, and feeding the hungry; and
19 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
20 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately recognized.
21 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
22 the members of this body recognize and commend Morris Roberts for his dedication to both
23 the community and the musical and cultural landscape of Georgia.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
25 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
26 Morris Roberts.
